description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to appoint a Rota Co-Ordinator for Surgery for 22.5 hours per week, who is committed, self-motivated and has excellent, friendly communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will entail covering for the Paediatric Rota Co-Ordinator in times of annual leave.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post holder will be based at Royal Albert Edward Infirmary working Monday - Friday.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful candidate will be responsible for providing a high standard of medical cover by the deployment/maximisation of medical staff resources within the division.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;the role will require you to work across all areas in the Trust which includes those that are designated as positive, asymptomatic and negative COVID wards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please Note: This vacancy may close earlier than the given closing date if a high level of applications are received.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Candidates will be asked to provide original qualifications at interview.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSimon McDermottJob titleDeputy Performance ManagerEmail addressSimon.mcdermott@wwl.nhs.ukTelephone number01942 82 2872&lt;/p&gt;
